# Whispa App 🎙️

[![PyPI Version](https://img.shields.io/pypi/v/whispa-app)](https://pypi.org/project/whispa-app/)
[![Python Versions](https://img.shields.io/pypi/pyversions/whispa-app)](https://pypi.org/project/whispa-app/)
[![License: MIT](https://img.shields.io/badge/License-MIT-yellow.svg)](https://opensource.org/licenses/MIT)
[![Downloads](https://pepy.tech/badge/whispa-app)](https://pepy.tech/project/whispa-app)
[![Windows Build](https://img.shields.io/badge/Windows-Installer-blue)](https://github.com/damoojeje/whispa_app/releases/latest)

A powerful desktop application for audio transcription and translation, powered by OpenAI's Whisper and MarianMT.

## ✨ Features

### 🎙️ Audio Transcription
- Support for multiple audio formats (WAV, MP3, M4A, FLAC, OGG)
- 5 Whisper model sizes for speed/accuracy tradeoff:
  - `tiny` (fast, less accurate)
  - `base` (balanced)
  - `small` (recommended)
  - `medium` (accurate)
  - `large` (most accurate)
- Real-time progress tracking
- Voice Activity Detection (VAD)

### 🌍 Translation
- Support for multiple languages:
  - English
  - Spanish
  - French
  - German
  - Chinese
  - Japanese
- Real-time translation progress
- Preserve formatting and timestamps

### 💾 Export Options
- Plain Text (.txt)
- SubRip Subtitles (.srt)
- WebVTT (.vtt)
- JSON with timestamps

### 🖥️ System Features
- Modern, responsive GUI
- Dark/Light theme
- Real-time system monitoring
- GPU acceleration (when available)
- Anonymous telemetry (opt-out available)

## 🚀 Installation

### Method 1: PyPI (Recommended)
```bash
# Install from PyPI
pip install whispa-app

# Launch the app
whispa
```

### Method 2: Windows Installer
1. Download the latest installer from [Releases](https://github.com/damoojeje/whispa_app/releases/latest)
2. Run `WhispaApp-Setup.exe`
3. Follow the installation wizard
4. Launch from Start Menu

### Method 3: From Source
```bash
# Clone the repository
git clone https://github.com/damoojeje/whispa_app
cd whispa_app

# Create virtual environment
python -m venv venv
source venv/bin/activate  # Linux/Mac
venv\Scripts\activate     # Windows

# Install dependencies
pip install -r requirements.txt

# Install in editable mode
pip install -e .

# Launch the app
whispa
```

## 📦 First Run

On first launch, Whispa App will:
1. Create necessary directories
2. Download required models (if not present)
3. Configure system settings

Models are downloaded on-demand to save disk space:
- Whisper models: 150MB - 2.9GB
- Translation models: ~300MB per language

## 🛠️ Development

### Setup Development Environment
```bash
# Install development dependencies
pip install -r requirements-dev.txt

# Install pre-commit hooks
pre-commit install
```

### Run Tests
```bash
pytest
```

### Build Documentation
```bash
cd docs
make html
```

### Build Windows Installer
```bash
python scripts/build_installer.py
```

## 📁 Project Structure
```
whispa_app/
├── src/
│   └── whispa_app/           # Main package
│       ├── __init__.py
│       ├── main.py           # Application entry
│       ├── transcription.py  # Whisper integration
│       ├── translation.py    # Translation logic
│       ├── device.py        # Hardware management
│       ├── telemetry.py     # Usage analytics
│       ├── utils.py         # Utilities
│       ├── exporters.py     # Export formats
│       ├── ui/              # User interface
│       └── assets/          # Resources
├── tests/                   # Test suite
├── docs/                    # Documentation
├── scripts/                 # Build scripts
└── requirements/            # Dependencies
```

